sql:
SELECT area_name
FROM community_areas
WHERE crime_rate > 0.05;

external_knowledge:
- "Open" incidents refer to those that are still under investigation and have not been resolved or closed; 
- "Theft" incidents include all types of theft crime; 
- Community areas are geographic divisions of a city or region for administrative and planning purposes; 
- The "most recent" incidents are determined by the date of occurrence.

- The comprehensive summary is expected to provide a detailed overview of each crime incident; 
- crime incidents are typically reported and investigated by law enforcement agencies; 
- the details included in the summary can be used for analysis, investigation, or record-keeping purposes; 
- geographical coordinates (latitude and longitude) can be used to map crime locations and analyze spatial patterns; 
- the most recent report details are included to provide an update on the current status of each incident.
